{"abstract":[{"text":"Returns whether ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"source"},{"type":"text","text":" has been destroyed."}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isDestroyed"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib14SourceProtocolPAAE11isDestroyedSbvp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib9SourceRefV","symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"isDestroyed","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef\/SourceProtocol-Implementations"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef\/isDestroyed","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"isDestroyed","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is important when you operate upon your objects","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from within idle handlers, but may have freed the object","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"before the dispatch of your idle handler."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["static gboolean","idle_callback (gpointer data)","{","  SomeWidget *self = data;","   ","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  \/\/ do stuff with self","  self->idle_id = 0;","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","   ","  return G_SOURCE_REMOVE;","}"," ","static void","some_widget_do_stuff_later (SomeWidget *self)","{","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  self->idle_id = g_idle_add (idle_callback, self);","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","}"," ","static void","some_widget_init (SomeWidget *self)","{","  g_mutex_init (&self->idle_id_mutex);","","  \/\/ ...","}","","static void","some_widget_finalize (GObject *object)","{","  SomeWidget *self = SOME_WIDGET (object);","   ","  if (self->idle_id)","    g_source_remove (self->idle_id);","   ","  g_mutex_clear (&self->idle_id_mutex);","","  G_OBJECT_CLASS (parent_class)->finalize (object);","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will fail in a multi-threaded application if the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"widget is destroyed before the idle handler fires due","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the use after free in the callback. A solution, to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this particular problem, is to check to if the source"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"has already been destroy within the callback.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"c","code":["static gboolean","idle_callback (gpointer data)","{","  SomeWidget *self = data;","  ","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  if (!g_source_is_destroyed (g_main_current_source ()))","    {","      \/\/ do stuff with self","    }","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  ","  return FALSE;","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calls to this function from a thread other than the one acquired by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] the [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] is attached to are typically","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"redundant, as the source could be destroyed immediately after this function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returns. However, once a source is destroyed it cannot be un-destroyed, so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this function can be used for opportunistic checks from any thread.","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/sourceref\/isdestroyed"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceRef/isDestroyed":{"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isDestroyed","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourceref\/isdestroyed","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns whether "},{"code":"source","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" has been destroyed.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","title":"isDestroyed","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef\/isDestroyed"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceRef/SourceProtocol-Implementations":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourceref\/sourceprotocol-implementations","title":"SourceProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef\/SourceProtocol-Implementations"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Source":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GSource","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data type"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"representing an event source.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Source","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/source","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Source"}],"title":"Source","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","title":"MainContext","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceRef":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourceref","title":"SourceRef","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceRef"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSource"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data type","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"representing an event source."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceRef"}]}}}